[...] what?
> An informal, casual gathering of Bus minded people.
> 
> Where?
> Tuckahoe State Park campgrounds, Marylands Eastern
> Shore.
> 
> When?
> 23-25 Aug 02
> 
> What can i expect?
> Level padded sites, water and trash on site, bathhouse
> with hot showers and an additional hot water tap
> ouside. Wooded, quiet campground :) rental cabins
> available. Dumping station.
> 
> Wildlife !!!! Bald Eagles !!! Whitetailed deer,
> beavers, muskrats, groundhogs, squirrels chipmunks,
> rabbits birds and more birds, and more furry little
> woodland creatures !! bring a camera :)
> 
> Activities - 
> canoeing: excellent canoe trails on upper and lower
> rivers, and on the marsh/lake itself. Canoe rentals
> thru park service available, and launch sites for your
> canoe.
> Trails - hiking, biking and horse trails run thru the
> entire park area.
> for the kids - many playgrounds
>  
> Adkins Arboretum - a 500 acre site in the park,
> displays and propagates trees, shrubs and plants
> native to Maryland.
> 
> I will be reserving a few sites next to each other. If
> more turn up, then i will ask for donations to help
> with the expense, but we can fit three per site :)
> 
> DIRECTIONS : 
> from Annapolis Maryland - take rt 50 east, across the
> Bay Bridge ($2.50 toll one way pay) to rt 404 east.
> Cross the Tuckahoe river, and at the top of the hill,
> turn left at the light (rt 480), make your first left
> (Eveland rd) to the T (its a couple miles), turn
> right, then an immediate left on Cherry Lane.
> campground is about a mile on the left, go straight
> back to the camping loop .. we will  wear a volkswagen
> bus so you know who we are :p
> 
> questions or requests for further information may be
> directed to vw_bear(-at-)yahoo.com
